<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/116853421-lisa"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1623601802i/116853421._UY100_CR45,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/116853421-lisa">Lisa</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Maeve Binchy is all about slowly building characters and description of places and daily life - often in Dublin. If you are more a plot kind of person<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Maeve Binchy is all about slowly building characters and description of places and daily life - often in Dublin. If you are more a plot kind of person, best not to read her books. If you like her style and you liked this book, read Quentin's. Picking up these books to reread them was like visiting old friends and reminiscing.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
