<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/52292729-michelle-edis"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1454550600i/52292729._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/52292729-michelle-edis">Michelle Edis</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">You will find, if you become a fan as much as I am, that several characters move in and out of her stories. Sometimes they are the stars of the show, <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">You will find, if you become a fan as much as I am, that several characters move in and out of her stories. Sometimes they are the stars of the show, sometimes they are mentioned as friends of friends etc.<br /><br />I have read every book she's ever written and at one point, I read them all in the order that they were written. This way, you get glimpses over and over of familiar characters as they live their lives and like a 'real' community, have many touchpoints and intertwining lives. <br /><br />I really, really, really love her work.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
