        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1605457123" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9551410459272556692">3.5 stars<br/><br/>Cathy Scarlet and Tom Feather are friends and are trying to start a catering business in Dublin. Cathy’s husband, Neil, has young cousins who show up at his rich parents’ place, needing a place to stay, but they rub his parents the wrong way, so Cathy and Neil end up taking them in. Tom’s wife, Marcella, wants desperately to be a model. <br/><br/>There is plenty going on, as this novel follows their lives for one year. There are many characters, and the perspective goes back and forth amongst man</span>
  <span id="freeText9551410459272556692" style="display:none">3.5 stars<br /><br />Cathy Scarlet and Tom Feather are friends and are trying to start a catering business in Dublin. Cathy’s husband, Neil, has young cousins who show up at his rich parents’ place, needing a place to stay, but they rub his parents the wrong way, so Cathy and Neil end up taking them in. Tom’s wife, Marcella, wants desperately to be a model. <br /><br />There is plenty going on, as this novel follows their lives for one year. There are many characters, and the perspective goes back and forth amongst many of them, but somehow, they are pretty easy to keep straight. I quite like that Binchy often has characters in multiple novels. I enjoyed the book, but problems can be seen coming from a bit of a distance. That is, I don’t think there are really any surprises in the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9551410459272556692" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


